column4: <content>Good Shepherd. The Good Shepherd gives his life for his herd, according to the gospel, but this is not usually represented. In Bruegel's print of 1565 he is fighting with the wolf, as also in C. Matsys's (?) painting in 1932 with Thomas Harries or in Hans Bol's drawing, but never is this shown being killed by the wolf. H. Bol, 2 drawings in Witt Collection, exh. R&A Flemish & Belgian Art 300-1900, 1927: 535 The Good Shepherd (20,2 x 30 cm); 538 The Hireling Shepherd (20,2 x 30,5 cm) cf. the prints from the Theatrum Biblicum of the same compositions with differences, by M. de Vos, engraved by Goltzius.</content>
